The paper deals with the Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP), which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of local consistency and AF-consistency checks, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and constraint programming (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of Taylor domains, which are objects of interest in mathematical logic and model theory, falling under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves the study of subinstances of the CSP, which can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem and falls under the category of discrete optimization (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
